A brother has spoken of the moment a seaside adventure turned to tragedy and his regrets at  leaving his sister trapped in a water-filled cave while he tried to get help.

Charlotte Furness-Smith, 30, died after she and her brother Alex were swept into the cave as they spent a day climbing sea cliffs.

The terrified former Royal Navy Reserve screamed ‘Get me out of here’, as rescuers spent two hours trying to reach her.

Her brother tried to summon help on his mobile phone but couldn’t get a signal. The 31-year-old decided to leave his sister, who was known as Buffy, while he dived underwater and swam out to get help.

