He told the inquest into his sister’s death yesterday: ‘Buffy was a bit scared but we talked and she calmed down. I told her it would be OK.

‘After a while it became apparent we could not keep being battered by the waves.

‘We had a mobile phone with us in a waterproof bag so we tried to dial 999 but there was no reception. We looked to swim out of the cave but every time we saw an opportunity another big wave came crashing in.

‘It appeared the only option was for one of us to swim outside to get help.

‘I decided to swim out of the cave. Buffy wanted to go with me. She said she could not bear not knowing if something had happened to me.

