‘I said that she should be able to see me going out and if I did get into danger she would have a second chance of getting out. I asked her to stay put. I thought that was the safest thing to do.’

Coastguards and lifeboat crews were unable to reach Miss  Furness-Smith because of the severe conditions and spoke to her through a blowhole in the top of the cave.

The inquest heard coastguard Ian Bugler risked his life by being lowered down the narrow hole.

